@Vampire Max hummed as he picked up a pen and began to write. "We need a plan; a good one too. Ian might be useless, but his thugs aren't... usually. Anyhow, first things first: How do we get in? We could sneak in... it gives us the upper hand and Ian wouldn't see it coming. However... we haven't been the greatest at this in the past..." Max scratches at his beard for a second. "We... We could try and get help from the outside. But that's risky. Most likely, it'd get back to Ian if we came with an army... hm... or maybe not an army... just someone powerful. I have a contact in mind, though I have no idea if they'll want to help us."
(-Aggressive buzzing-

"Both options seem like they could work, but I agree they are rather risky. Both outcomes due have their pros and cons." Zahir thought for a moment. "We haven't heard from those mages in awhile, and the werewolves were pretty good with weapons...as I can remember... but that might cause Ian and his thugs to get suspicious, if Ian even notices. If we go to sneak in there is a chance we'd encounter his thugs, but even if we get passed him it would still be 4 against who knows how many people." 

//😀👍//

Max nodded. "True. Keep in mind we have no idea if either the mages or the werewolves have people to spare. With everything going on, we'd be lucky to get one of their weakest. Like I said I have a... contact... that might be willing to help us, but nothing is guaranteed. They don't trust us, I barely trust them. Sneaking in does have it's advantages, depending on where Ian is located. If it's at the pub, well, that's easy. We have lots of ways to sneak around. However... if he's at the hotel... Hm... I have ways of getting in and out, but it'll be tricky." Max sighs as he writes down more, making notes as he goes. "I can't believe I have to do this for a *second* time." He mumbles.

"Ian tends to be suspicious of those who are smarter than him, stronger. Anyone who poses a threat to him or his empire. And unfortunately... well..." Max hesitates and take a deep breath. "He has a dossier on every single one of you. On your strengths, weaknesses, how they can be used against you, people you're close to, things you care about, your fighting styles, everything. I know because I wrote them."

Becca sighed, rubbing her face in her hands. *Max was only doing his job* she reminded herself. "I really wish this didn't have to happen, but Ian has stepped way out of line. I agree that an army would probably alert him, but I also agree that sneaking isn't always the best option for our team, either. Who is this other contact you speak of? I doubt you would have brought them up if you didn't have *some* bit of trust that they could help us, and the way I see it, this would probably go best with a small but powerful attack force."

Max froze. He's eyes narrowed and his aura became cold. His writing hand stopped and his grip on the pencil tightened. After a few moments of tense silence, the man growled through clenched teeth: "Channard..Can...Come....Here." The words looked as though they physical pained him to say.

Becca's eyes snapped up. "Sorry, sorry, I'll just..." Becca buried her head in her hands as she tried not to cry at Max's harsh tone. She didn't mean to hurt his feelings, or whatever reaction that was.
At the sudden snap on the room's tone, the small yellow eyed cat, Lele let out a small meow from near Becca's feet.
Max sighed. "Sorry, I...I shouldn't have done that. This is not easy for me, but I shouldn't have reacted like that."
Becca peered down under the table to the cat, gently scooting her chair back and patting her lap hesitantly as she formulated her reply. "It's... okay. It's been a tough night for all of us."

The cat looked up to her with it's big yellow eyes and let out a happy meow, as it jumped up and landed effortlessly. As soon as it got there, Lele layed down and began to gently knead her paws against Becca's sweater, purring loudly.

"Its not. I need to get better with my anger." Max watched the cat jump up, and a genuine smile graced his face. Quietly, as though he'd frighten Lele if he was too loud, he said: "Lele's never reacted that way to anyone before."
Becca sniffled with a smile and gently scratched behind Lele's ears and then under her chin. "I appreciate that you see that you need to change, Max. It's ok to be angry sometimes, though. I get it."

Becca set aside the heavy conversation in favor of the seratonin-inducing fluffball on her lap. "I don't think I've ever said how much I love animals. Specifically cats, dogs, and strangely enough, birds. They are all so precious. I don't have much experience with them, though."
Lele practically chased Becca's hand with her head, giving her kitten licks whenever Becca was in tounge range.

Standing, Max pulled his phone out and tapped on it a few times, before typing something and clicking call. The phone rang as he leaned on the kitchen counter.
-The phone rang for a good few moments, yet eventually someone did pick up. The voice that answered was recognizable, calm when answering- *”Hello?”*
"I need your help." Max drummed his fingers on the counter.
-The voice seemed to recognize Max and there was a pause, then a response- *”You-? How did you even get my number-?”* -They seemed confused, yet there was a hint of resentment in their tone-
"Ian's being dethroned, possibly murdered. I need your help." Max  said plainly, as though this was an every day thing.
*”Why do I even ask.”* -They muttered, then continued- *”How did this come about?”*
"Come over here and find out. You in?" He paused. "And I'm sure you know what will happen to you if I find you speak a word of this to anyone, in or not."

*”Of course I’m aware, nor do I plan to tell anyone about this. Do you even have a plan of action?”* -They were cautious about this. Without a plan, everything would fall to shreds with or without his help. He wanted to make sure this wasn’t a loose cannon, plus Max and himself were on.. iffy terms-
Max huffed. "Of course I- *we* have a plan. Are. You. In?"
*”Oh, it’s a we now?”*
"In. Or Out? You got three seconds."
*”Alright, fine, I’m in. Only because I dislike Ian with a burning passion.”* -He soon gave his verdict after a moment of thought, as he only had 3 seconds to do so-
"Good. Meet me at..." Max provided his address through grit teeth, along with the time.
*”Noted. I’ll be sure to be there.”*
He hung up with an annoyed sigh. "Alright. He'll be here."
